LAGOS  – Dana Air has been recognised for its outstanding services and collaborations over the years by Mrs. Rejoice Ndudinachi, the Manager of the Sam Mbakwe International Cargo Airport in Owerri, Imo state. Speaking on the award to Dana Air, Ndudinachi said Dana Air has been outstanding in terms of their service delivery at the Sam Mbakwe International Cargo Airport in Owerri and willing, available to support when the need arises. A statement by Mr. Kingsley Ezenwa, the Communication Manager, Dana Air said that Ndudinachi appreciated the airline’s support and its outstanding service delivery to its customers in Owerri and encouraged it to keep up the good work. Receiving the award on behalf of Dana Air, Kingsley Adichie, the Acting Station Manager of the airline’s Owerri Station, assured that Dana Air would continue to work with the Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) in Owerri to not only achieve efficient service delivery across board for passengers, but strengthen the smooth working relationship that both teams have enjoyed over the years. He appreciated FAAN for being supportive as always and finding Dana Air a worthy partner in progress.